narrativeSections.additionalInfo: Welcome! This guided tutorial will place you into an urban environment with four injured patients that require your medical care. This guided practice will help you understand the gameplay and controls for the simulation. Listen carefully and follow the prompts.

Now that you are in the environment, please walk forward slowly until you see a blue grid. This barrier will serve as a reminder of your physical space and boundaries. Now take a few steps back until the grid disappears.
You can start your SALT triage protocol by shouting a sort command to the victims. Start with a walk order by saying: “If you can move, walk to the safe zone!”
Now order a wave command. Face the victims and say: “If you can hear me, wave your hand!”

Now that you know how to strafe, let's try teleporting instead. Feel around on your right controller for a thumb joystick. The right joystick is for teleporting which is helpful for longer movements.  If you hold the right joystick forward, you will see a green beam of light that shows where you will move. When you release the right stick, you will teleport to the targeted area. Try moving to the unresponsive patient in the distance.

You need to first assess the vital signs of this unresponsive patient. Put your hand on their wrist or neck to take a pulse. Your hand pose will change and the controller will vibrate. Feel the patient's pulse now.

You also need to assess their breathing. You can do this asking the patient how their breathing is. If they are unresponsive, closely observe the movement of their chest. Their chest will rise and fall.

You assessed this patient's vitals and now it's time for you to treat them. You have a triage bag containing medical gear. It is located at your right hip. To open, look down and place your right hand down by the white bag at your right hip. It will highlight yellow. Pull and hold the controller's front trigger down. Keep holding your trigger and bring your hand up into view. Observe the open bag attached to your hand. The black open bag and its medical tools should now be visible.

narrativeSections.sectionDescription: Learn to use the triage kit

narrativeSections.additionalInfo: Release the trigger to let go of the bag. It will stay in place. Try that now.

Notice the contents of the bag. On top are tools and gear to treat patients. On the bottom are triage tags. If you hover your hand over a tool it will highlight yellow. Information about its use and supply count will be displayed inside the bag. Now, hover over a tool then pull and hold the trigger down to grab it.
The tool is now attached to your hand. To return it to the bag, let go of the trigger. The tool will automatically return to the bag and your supply count will be reset.
If you walk too far away from the bag it will automatically return to your hip. You can also strafe with the left joystick to have it return immediately.

narratorRadioAudio.audioClip: Universal Tutorial Audio/Return Bag to Hip

narrativeSections.sectionDescription: Wait for any additional bag exploration

narrativeSections.additionalInfo: Treat the unresponsive patient by selecting the decompression needle from the bag and placing it on their chest.
You need to move to the next victim. There is an alert patient sitting nearby. Approach them.
There is a US Marine crushed under concrete nearby. He needs to be dragged to safety. Move to his position and work with the uninjured Marine to help him.

narratorRadioAudio.audioClip: Universal Tutorial Audio/Patient 3 - Move to Position

narrativeSections.additionalInfo: You are responsible for treating all patients. The other marine outside is uninjured but the young girl that walked to safety still needs your help. Return to her by strafing and teleporting and provide treatment.

narratorRadioAudio.audioClip: Universal Tutorial Audio/Patient 4 - Return to Her
